reviewText:
Small review:
This is, currently, the BEST platform shooter in the world. Playing it since 'bout 2009.
Give it a try.

Big Review:
Good things:
2D platformer
Beautiful graphics
Nice physics
Very high skillcap
Absolutely free, nothing to pay.
Open source
High performance even on bad computers
Nice community
5094839054389053 modified servers, with dozens of gamemodes
You can modify game graphics freely, and there are lots of skins for download
Customized clients (non-steam)
Bad things:
Sometimes there are hackers, but its rare and they can be easily kicked
Sometimes there are no near servers, and you may get a high ping
As the game has a high skill cap, and the game is very old, you may have a hard time playing vs good/old players
Updates are slow (If you're a C++ programmer, help on the development![www.teeworlds.com])
Overall rating: 10/10, one of the best games I've ever played.

reviewText: I'm playing this game for many years now and I don't get enough from it. For everyone who complains about, that the enemies are too good:\n\nDisable the filters and play DDRace" or anything that sounds similar. It's a game mode
date:
where the only goal is to reach the end and its coop => no enemies and it teaches you very important movement. Maybe use the spectator mode to see how other people are doing it and try to do the same.

Another advice: increase your mouse sensivity. It's important in this game to move your mouse everywhere on the screen very fast.

Cheaters aren't actually that common. It's quite easy to see if someone uses an aimbot and you can votekick them. With most weapons the bot doesn't help you much anyway. But of course if you play very well people just assume you cheat
recommended: because you learned to move very fast.\n\nAlso don't try to play this game with a ping>100. I find no fun in it."

reviewText:
This is a game where you are a Kirby who brutally murders other Kirbies to death with Hammers, Guns, Grenade Launchers, Lasers and even Katanas.

This is one of those games which is super easy to understand, yet is very hard to master as I am constantly learning new tricks, maneuvers and ways to play.

Pros:
- Runs well on lower end PC's
- Runs god damn gloriously on my computer, at its worst I get 500 fps... So you will have no problems running it.
- Cute art style and characters.
- Fun to play.
- Does not take up much space on your storage drive.
- Very casual game.
- Tonnes of fun mods on the internet.
- Good Community.
- winning requires skill, there is absolutely no pay to win in this game.
- Open-Source
- Grappling hook mechanics are SO FUN!

Cons:
- Hacks, there are way to many Aimbots / Spinbots out there, and it really does ruin the game and enjoyment of the game.
- Addictive.
- Hard to host your own server.

I would really reccomend this game to most people as it is really easy to learn how to play and is a good bit of fun.

10/10 Would play again

4. 1/4 cup water

6. 1 pinch salt
7. 5 apples - peeled, cored and sliced
8. 1 pastry for double-crust pie

Directions:
1. Preheat oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C).
2. Combine butter, white sugar, brown sugar, water, cinnamon, and salt in a saucepan over medium heat. Bring to a boil, remove from heat and set aside.
3. Roll out half the pastry to fit a 9-inch pie plate. Place bottom crust in pie plate; pour in apple slices.
4. Roll out top crust into a 10-inch circle. Cut into 8 (1-inch) wide strips with a sharp paring knife or pastry wheel. Weave the pastry strips, one at a time, into a lattice pattern. Fold the ends of the lattice strips under the edge of the bottom crust and crimp to seal.
5. Pour butter-sugar mixture over top of pie, coating the lattice, and allowing any remaining sauce to drizzle through the crust.
6. Bake in the preheated oven for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C), and bake until the crust is golden brown, the caramel on the top crust is set, and the apple filling is bubbling, 35 to 40 more minutes. Allow to cool completely before slicing.

reviewText:
Teeworlds was one of the games that got me into multiplayer gaming waay back in 2012. Excuse my game hours; I have hundreds more non-Steam.

Teeworlds is a 2D, free, online multiplayer, deathmatch-style game in which you control your own personal, cute, Kirby-like Tee that shoots regular guns, lazars, grenade launchers, and shotguns. Of course, all of the typical gamemodes are there: deathmatch, team deathmatch, capture the flag... But what I found to be the most interesting is the modded gamemodes (because Teeworlds is opensource). I was  spending a more on Infected (one person starts out as a zombie and slowly infects everyone else), DDRace (a gamemode in which you attempt to clear an obstacle course), and some of the other gamemodes than the original ones.

Anyway, play this game? Please? You're REALLY missing out if you don't.

One of the best, most free games on steam. There are no IAP'S. there are no crates. There are no purchasable hats. There is no pay to win. It's blissfully simplistic.

It's a 2D team shooter with one of my favorite mechanics ever: Grappling Hooks. Grapples are one of those mechanics thats easy to use, yet really hard to master. the average player will start out with uing it to boost jumps, and within a few weeks of playing adapt to it and can go across, even under the map better and faster than rocket jumping in Tf2. Despite being old , it still has a small but dedicated playerbase, meaning whenever i wanted to play, i could. all this, plus plenty of FREE customization items, for only 6MB on your drive!
PROS:
5 different weapons
GRAPPLING HOOKS!
Free as Free can be
Dedicated playerbase
easy to pick up, hard to master.
takes up no space
CONS:
Small playerbase
Lack of Team balance (yes it will make you wish you had TF2's teambalance. 7v3 happened while writing this review)

My friend got me into this game, and it's pretty darn fun. Basically, you're this little Kirby that fights other Kirbys in currently 3 gamemodes: Deathmatch, Team Deathmatch, and Capture the Flag. All of these gamemodes are pretty simple, so you should get the hang of it in no time. In DM and TDM (Deathmatch and Team Deathmatch), you start off with only two weapons; the hammer and a pistol. The pistol has infinite ammo, but it does pretty low damage. Use this if you run out of ammo with the different weapons. The hammer's pretty good at chipping health off, but nobody has the decency for a 1v1 fair hammer battle, so only use it if they're focusing on someone else or you got them trapped. There's other weapons that you have to find place around the map. There's a shotgun, a grenade launcher, a sniper rifle, I think, and there's the almighty, god slaying, ♥♥♥♥ destroying, noob wrecking that came from Satan's ♥♥♥ that he uses daily to sharpen his horns and his nipples for the ladies. It's a sword. But not just any sword. It's a powerful one. It takes off like a billion hit points, so you're lucky if you survive at least one of them. When it's being used, the user can charge at foes at blinding speed, so your only hope is for some other poor sucker to grab the attention of the wielder. It's a pretty rare find, so if you find it, then by all means, TAKE IT. There's also a hook, which you can grab on to lots of things like ceilings or walls, and even people. When used on a person, it takes them to you. Or it takes you to them. I forgot which. It's pretty much your best movement option, since you're flying around like Spiderman. There's also your health bar and an armor bar. Both can be collected from pieces around the map. The armor takes a few hits for you, depending on how much pieces of armor you have, so it's especially useful for surviving the Xx_$w0rD0fd00M_Xx. In Capture the Flag, (CTF), you start off with all these weapons, except for the sword, of course. The controls are pretty simple, and just about anybody can run this game at a lot of FPS, even me, with a potato for a computer. It literally installs in seconds, so...\nInstall it!
It's got grappling hooks, grenade launchers, and giant wooden mallets. What more could you ask for?

Teeworlds is actually a very fun game to play. The game's graphics is simple, allowing most PCs to run the game without having to install advanced graphic cards (e.g. Nvidia/ATI Radeon). Also, the game file is very small, (about 9 MB), allowing users to download the game for only a short period of time. The game engine is based on game engines used to make online 2D platformer games (e.g. Plazma Burst 2/Raze); so, the game shouldn't be hard to play. What this game is needs right now is more players, more weapons,  more maps (maybe?) and of course, what we all love so much, Hats. Lovely, beautiful hats for the characters to wear. But other than that, I HIGHLY recommend this game for others to try out.

I used to rage hard at this game, purely because of the amount of lag I ALWAYS had to deal with. But I got some advice in-game to download the ddnet client and use that instead of the Steam version, and it has changed my whole experience. Now I fly through maps with ease and have a no trouble dodging and firing.
The thing about this game is the huge differences in skill levels. The guys you see absolutely destroying everyone have been playing for a while and will probably wreck you every time. But then one day they won't be able to. And it will feel great.
The day I jumped up from an average player to that skill was the day I turned my mouse sensitivity riiiight up. There was an instant improvement in my movement and accuracy. Then downloading the ddnet client has possibly put me almost on par with the pros. Still have the issue of lag to deal with always, since nobody in my country really plays this game, but I have great fun anyway.

This was one of my first games. I'm still new to Steam, and I think this is a good place to start. Teeworlds is fun, fast, and fun to play. However, I would enjoy to see more games, maps, etc.

Tl;dr:
You should get this game as it has little-no lag, great looking graphics and amazing gameplay. It is opensource and has it's own map editor (ctrl + shift + e). It is easy to learn, difficult to master!
Pros(+) & Cons(-)
+Nice community
+Pretty Graphics
+Comes with editor
+Big modding community (You can drive vehicles made of armour & hearts!)
+Fun and easy to learn
+Hard to master
+Grappling hooks
+Fast paced gameplay
+Slow gameplay
+Weapons: Hammer, Ninja sword, Pistol, Shotgun, Grenade Launcher, Laser Rifle and hooks
+You can get skins for pretty much everything, for free
+No microtransactions
+Enough servers alive to be great
+Takes up hardly any space
+FREE!
+Windows, Linux, and mac!
-A lot of servers are dead
-Editor requires online tutorials as there is no tutorial inside it
-Hosting a server is not always easy
-You may end up raging :P

peice of ♥♥♥♥ game\n

Characters:

Little blobs wih feet. Can be colored and dressed in different ways

Controls:

A and D for Left and Right, Space to jump, Rightclick to use a grappling hook. Leftclick to shoot. Controls rebindable

Weapons:

6 unique weapons: Rifle, Hammer, Grenade Launcher, Laser Gun, Shotgun and a very rare Katana

Gamemodes:

(Team) Deathmatch, Capture the Flag and Community gamemodes like Race

Community:

Lots of servers. Generally friendly people

Technical:

Comic design. Simple sound effects. Good servers

Verdict:

Really fun 2D multiplayer shooter. And its FREE. So you can atleast try it out, can't you? :D

I've been playing for a couple years now and this is what is good and bad in my opinion:
Pros:
-Fun to play

-No DLC's
-Beautiful graphics
-Nice physics
-Great forum and community
-Open source
-Many skins to download

Cons:
-A bit slow in updates
-The game is old and has high skill cap, so might get owned the first time playing

Out of all i recommend this game 100% 10/10 for everyone.
